|stock_os=Linux;2.6.36; |tp_firmware=Padavan |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ssid=ASUS |default_ssid_regex=^ASUS$ |default_ip=192.168.1.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin |oui=38:2C:4A,54:A0:50 |oui_eth=38:2C:4A,54:A0:50 }} {{TagLine|3-in-1 Router/AP/Range Extender for Large Environment}} :[http://www.asus.com/Networking/RTN11P/ Product Page] (RT-N11P) {{•}} [http://www.asus.com/Networking/RT-N11P-B1/ Product Page] (RT-N11P B1) "AP699E8N3.BT267-4", "REV.1.0" and "1433" is silkscreened on the board. {{see also|ASUS RT-N11P B1|ASUS RT-N12+|ASUS RT-N300}} ===Overview=== * Multiple 3-in-1 Router/Access Point/Range Extender wireless modes * Two external 5dBi antennas for more powerful and wider coverage * 4 SSIDs help manage bandwidth allocation and access control ===Reviews=== *[http://www.ixbt.com/comm/asus-rt-n11p.shtml On '''iXBT'''] (tested [https://code.google.com/p/rt-n56u/ FW 3.4.3.9-091 base] by '''Padavan''') *[http://foxnetwork.ru/index.php/en/component/content/article/184-asus-rt-n11p.html On '''FoxNetWork'''] (images PCB) :"AP699E8N3.BT267-4", "REV.1.0", "ASKPCB" and "1433" :(08/2014) is silkscreened on the board in the photos. ===Forum threads=== * [http://forum.ixbt.com/topic.cgi?id=14:60674-4#90 RTN's post on '''iXBT''' forums] * [http://forum.ixbt.com/topic.cgi?id=14:62022-10#303 Padavan's post on '''iXBT''' forums] :[[MediaTek]] MT7620N WiSoC is clocked 580/600MHz :CPU: MT7620N(H) rev.0206 @600/120MHz (stock @580/116MHz) :RAM: ''ESMT'' M12L2561616A-6T (32МB SDRAM, max 166MHz) :Flash: ''Macronix'' MX25L6406E (8MB SPI NOR, max 80MHz) :Quartz: 20MHz ===Serial=== ====Boot log (FW by Padavan)==== {{SCollapse|boot log |
